 5px;"></div><div class="labelHeader">Description:</div><div class="normalText"><p>Title: Bilingual Eligibility Assistant</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Location: Merrillville IN</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Travel: no</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Remote Work Option: no</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Job Description**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Located in the inbound change centers and local State offices, Bilingual Eligibility Assistants (EAs) serve as the customer service/front office specialists that are the first point of contact for clients visiting or calling the facility. An EA is responsible for directing clients to the appropriate department(s), review information providing by client for accuracy and completeness, assisting clients in accessing computer applications, and explaining program requirements to clients. Among other duties, EAs will receive, sort, and route mail, maintain office resources and machinery, and verify client information in State Eligibility Systems.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Key responsibilities**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Supports application and change processing by reviewing, accepting, receipting, sorting, and routing applications, changes, and redeterminations.</p><p>+ Performs receptionist and mail clerk duties</p><p>+ Identifies missing information and notifies clients to submit information to complete case actions.</p><p>+ Meets deadlines associated with case actions.</p><p>+ Complete work within quality standards set by the manager and state</p><p>+ Answers inquiries by clarifying desired information; researching, locating, and providing information by accessing State Eligibility Systems.</p><p>+ Resolves problems by clarifying issues; researching and exploring answers and alternative solutions; implementing solutions; escalating unresolved problems.</p><p>+ Fulfills requests by clarifying desired information; completing transactions; forwarding requests.</p><p>+ Provides exceptional customer service.</p><p>+ Follows all approved standard operating procedures and other applicable state and federal regulations.</p><p>+ Informs clients by explaining procedures; answering questions; providing information.</p><p>+ Maintains and improves quality results by adhering to standards and guidelines; recommending improved procedures</p><p>+ Updates job knowledge by studying new scripts; participating in educational opportunities</p><p>+ Effectively communicate with both internal and external clients</p><p>+ Consistently provide accurate and timely documentation of daily activities and results</p><p>+ Maintain accountability, reliability and dependability when performing all assigned job duties</p><p>+ Participate in training sessions required by the State and Cognosante</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>The successful candidate will also be expected to:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Pass a background check.</p><p>+ Successfully complete mandatory training and certification requirements in allotted timeframe.</p><p>+ Be available to work flexible shifts between 7am and 6 pm.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Minimum Qualifications**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Possess an Associates&#226; degree from an accepted and accredited college or university, OR the equivalent of six months customer service experience</p><p>+ Demonstrated fluency in Spanish and English</p><p>+ Ability to demonstrate proficiency in computer literacy, use of relevant computer applications such as MS Office, and use of other types of office technology</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Additional Qualifications**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Have working knowledge of Temporary Assistance for Needy Families (TANF), Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP), Medicaid programs, Hoosier Healthwise, Healthy Indiana Plan (HIP), or Indiana Manpower and Comprehensive Training (IMPACT)</p><p>+ Excellent communication skills and interpersonal skills</p><p>+ Ability to express ideas in clear and concise manner</p><p>+ Ability to problem-solve and to think tactically and identify significant success factors</p><p>+ Able to handle multiple tasks</p><p>+ Ability to handle ambiguity and change</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Requisition ID:** R0001155</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/frca-apply/bjthj4" id="ApplyBottomLink" target="_blank" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="javascript:setTimeout(&quot;window.location.href = &#39;/post-resume?jid=bjthj4&#39;;&quot;,1500); return true;">Go to apply&nbsp;<img src="/Images/applyarrow.png" height="21x;" width="16px;" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px;" class="sideBar"><div style="text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-left:5px;"><h4 style="padding-bottom:7px;">Similar Jobs</h4><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bjqkta/receptionist-lotus-highland-in-46322" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;0&#39;);">Receptionist</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" class="colorLocation">Highland, IN</span><span style="font-size:small;color:black"> - receptionist, lotus, notes, mail, computer, word,...</span></p><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bja8m2/receptionist-lotus-mail-send-highland-in" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;1&#39;);">Receptionist</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" class="colorLocation">Highland, IN</span><span style="font-size:small;color:black"> - receptionist, lotus, mail, escrow, estate, office,...</span></p><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/biy747/receptionist-enterprises-gary-in-46401" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;2&#39;);">Receptionist</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" class="colorLocation">Gary, IN</span><span style="font-s